  "@openshift/dynamic-plugin-sdk-webpack": "^5.0.0"All the newer webpack SDK versions require webpack 5.100+ and TS 5.9+. That's too invasive an upgrade. The simplest fix is to make the existing validation pass. Since `react` is a singleton with `allowFallback: false`, the validation requires the installed React to satisfy the SDK's dependency range (`^17.0.1`). 

The cleanest approach: downgrade React to 17.x to satisfy the SDK, but that would break PF6 which needs React 18. Instead, let me just patch the validation to not fail on this check, since this is a build-time check and at runtime the console provides the React instance.

